DOM (Document Object Model) is a tree-like representation of an HTML document. Every HTML element becomes an object (node) that JavaScript can access and manipulate.
Document → Entire webpage.
html → Root element.
head → Contains metadata.
title → Browser tab title.
body → Visible page content.
h1 and p → Child elements of body.
Text inside elements becomes text nodes.
structure
Document
│
└── html
    │
    ├── head
    │   └── title
    │       └── "DOM Example"
    │
    └── body
        ├── h1
        │   └── "Welcome to DOM"
        │
        └── p
            └── "This is a paragraph."